Mireles, an acquaintance of the man, was arrested December 31 on the felony charge. 

She later was released from the San Patricio County jail on a $3,500 bond.

The necklace was returned to the man's widow. 

'To watch my mother's shaking hands when the detective placed that chain back into them, I just felt a huge relief for my mother that the necklace was back where it was supposed to be,' Hartt said.

 

